{"lemma":"حاطِبٌ","slug":"حاطِبٌ","root":"ح.ط.ب","root_slug":"ح-ط-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ح-ط-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":false},"wiktextract":{"found":false},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n8381"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D8%AD%D8%A7%D8%B7%D9%90%D8%A8%D9%8C"}},"translations":null,"definition":null,"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n8381","headword_ar":"حَاطِبٌ","root":"HTb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"A collector of firewood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb, TA:) and so ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~aAbN","text_ar":"حَطَّابٌ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (A, Msb,) but in an intensive sense: (Msb:) or the latter,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who collects and sells firewood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaT~aAbapN","text_ar":"حَطَّابَةٌ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a company of collectors of firewood:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, Mgh:) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A_imaA='N","text_ar":"اـِمَا=ءٌ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HawaATibu","text_ar":"حَوَاطِبُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"[pl. of"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaATibapN","text_ar":"حَاطِبَةٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"female slaves who collect firewood."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, TA.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"huwa HaATibu layolK","text_ar":"هُوَ حَاطِبُ لَيْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He is one who confuses in his speech,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(A, K,) and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"in his affair:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"one who speaks what is bad and what is good:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, TA:) like him who collects firewood by night; (TA;) for this person sees not what he collects in his rope, (S, TA,) so he collects bad and good. (TA.) Az says, one who acts unjustly towards himself is likened to a collector of wood by night, because the latter may chance to put his hand upon a viper, and be bitten by it: and so is one who does not restrain his tongue, but censures others; by doing which a man sometimes occasions his own death. (TA.) It is said in a prov.,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlmikovaAru","text_ar":"المِكْثَارُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"HaATibu layolK","text_ar":"حَاطِبُ لَيْلٍ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"The loquacious is"},{"kind":"text","text":"[like]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a collector of firewood by night."},{"kind":"text","text":"(A 'Obeyd, TA.)"}],"source_refs":["Msb","TA","A","S","Mgh","K"]}]},"classical_definitions":null}